The main innovations of this study are twofold. First, it utilizes LLMs to develop an AI lexicon for commercial banks. Based on this
lexicon, this study mines information from bank annual reports and patent texts to construct indicators of bank AI adoption from two
perspectives: strategic orientation and innovation actions. This approach provides a comprehensive depiction of banks’ strategic
planning and practical application in the AI field. Second, this study thoroughly examines the potential impact of AI adoption on bank
profitability, not only investigating the direct effects and underlying mechanisms but also fully considering the differences among
various types of banks and across different regions, aiming to reveal the heterogeneous effects of AI adoption on bank profitability.
2. Hypothesis development
This study examines how AI adoption affects bank profitability through three mediating mechanisms: operating costs, income
diversity, and mobile banking development.
First, AI adoption directly reduces labor costs and enhances operational efficiency by optimizing bank processes, such as automating
core business segments like customer service, loan approval, and risk management (Fraisse and Laporte, 2022; Gomber et al.,
2018; K¨ onigstorfer and Thalmann, 2020; Lessmann et al., 2015; Manser Payne et al., 2021). Meanwhile, AI-driven data analytics
enable banks to achieve precise marketing and deliver personalized customer service, thereby effectively improving customer satisfaction
and loyalty (Gomber et al., 2018; Tong and Yang, 2025), which in turn expands the scale of low-cost funds such as demand
deposits and reduces bank deposit funding costs.
Second, AI adoption drives banks to continuously innovate financial products and services, such as launching robo-advisors and
personalized wealth management products (Gomber et al., 2018; Northey et al., 2022). These innovations help banks expand
non-interest income channels and diversify revenue sources, thereby enhancing overall bank profitability. By providing diversified
financial products and services, banks can reduce over-reliance on traditional interest income, enhance the stability and sustainability
of their income, and reduce operational risks while improving long-term returns.
Finally, AI adoption enhances mobile banking user experience, thereby boosting user adoption and engagement (Lee and Chen,
2022). For example, intelligent customer service can provide instant and efficient responses to user inquiries, and personalized recommendations
can enhance the accuracy of service matching. As the quality of mobile banking services improves, increases in the
number of active users, launch count, and usage duration can encourage greater engagement in activities like payments, fund transfers,
and investment management, thereby generating additional revenue opportunities for banks.
H1. AI adoption enhances bank profitability.
