3. Study design
3.1. Sample selection
This study uses panel data from 430 Chinese commercial banks from 2007 to 2022. The primary data source is the Wind database,
supplemented by the CSMAR database, the CNRDS database, and individual bank annual reports to address missing values. The mobile
banking data is sourced from Analysys Qianfan, a leading third-party data analytics platform specializing in the Chinese digital
economy. The initial sample is processed as follows: (1) Banks with fewer than three years of observations for key variables are
excluded. (2) All continuous variables are winsorized at the 1st and 99th percentiles. By the end of 2022, the total assets of the sample
banks represented 92.56 % of the total assets of Chinese commercial banks.
3.2. Definition of key variables
This study employs a text analysis methodology to construct a specialized lexicon for AI adoption in commercial banks, leveraging
the LLMs Claude 3.5 Sonnet and GPT-4o (see Appendix A for details). Through a series of systematic filtering, identification, and
integration steps, the final lexicon contains 136 representative AI-related terms. Based on this lexicon, the proportion of AI terms in the
full text of bank annual reports is used as a proxy variable for banks’ AI strategic orientation. Meanwhile, to capture banks’ innovation
actions in the AI field, the number of AI patents applied for by banks in the same year (processed by adding 1 and taking the natural
logarithm) is used as another proxy variable.
Return on assets (ROA) and return on equity (ROE) are the primary financial indicators for assessing bank profitability. ROA
measures the efficiency of bank asset management and the ability to generate profits from assets. ROE directly reflects the bank’s
ability to generate profits for shareholders and serves as a key metric for shareholders to assess investment returns. This study employs
both indicators to comprehensively assess bank profitability and financial health from the perspectives of asset management and
shareholder returns.
Detailed definitions of all variables are provided in Table 1, and Appendix Table B presents the descriptive statistical analysis.
