To examine the impact of AI adoption on bank profitability, this study constructs the following baseline regression equation,
estimated using ordinary least squares (OLS):
Profitabilityi,t =α +β ×AIi,t +γ ×Xi,t +θt +θi +εi,t (1)
where Profitabilityi,t is the dependent variable, representing the profitability of bank i in year t, specifically measured by ROA and ROE.
AIi,t is the independent variable, indicating the level of AI adoption of bank i in year t, comprehensively measured from the two dimensions:
strategic orientation and innovation actions. Xi,t denotes control variables, included to account for other factors that may
affect bank profitability. α is the constant intercept term, θt denotes year fixed effects, θi denotes bank fixed effects, and εi,t is the
random error term.
4. Empirical results
4.1. Baseline regression
This study aims to examine the impact of AI adoption on bank profitability. The regression results in Table 2 show that the coefficients
for AI adoption strategic orientation (AIRatio) and AI adoption innovation actions (lnAIApply) are positive and statistically
significant at the 1 % level. This indicates that both strategic orientation and practical technological application in AI significantly
contribute to enhancing bank profitability, thereby supporting research hypothesis H1. Regarding the control variables, higher asset
size (lnTotalAssets), deposits-to-assets ratio (DepositToAsset), and GDP growth rate (CityGDPG) generally have a significant positive
impact on bank profitability.
